Using the strip command on a string variable 
it will remove all of the specified characters 
in the arguments from either side of the main 
text, if left blank it will just remove the white 
space on either side. the replace method will
replace the first character in the argument with
the second specified character in the argument.


text = ".. Pirate .."


striped = text.strip(".")

replaced = text.replace("i","o")

print(striped) #will print "Pirate"

print(replaced) #will print ".. Porate .."